1
00:00:09,382 --> 00:00:11,700
If someone cried in your place,

2
00:00:14,034 --> 00:00:15,081
how would you feel?

3
00:00:16,038 --> 00:00:18,077
Who, P’? Daotok?

4
00:00:20,742 --> 00:00:22,454
Kram’s coming back to Thailand.

5
00:00:22,743 --> 00:00:25,845
It wasn’t easy clearing my schedule to go to California.

6
00:00:26,008 --> 00:00:27,560
You’re not gonna ditch me, right?

7
00:00:28,549 --> 00:00:32,601
In return for helping you, I have one condition.

8
00:00:32,903 --> 00:00:33,851
What condition?

9
00:00:35,229 --> 00:00:37,648
- Help me block my ex.
- Huh?

10
00:00:39,570 --> 00:00:41,340
Help me keep my ex away.

11
00:00:41,680 --> 00:00:42,150
Huh?

12
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:48,180
What do you mean?

13
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,300
Keep him from messing with you.

14
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:51,400
Mm.

15
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:53,040
Shit, why?

16
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:55,160
Is he really that persistent?

17
00:00:59,730 --> 00:01:01,810
Fine.

18
00:01:02,770 --> 00:01:05,230
What do you even call this?

19
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,630
A guard dog.

20
00:01:07,020 --> 00:01:08,320
Yeah.

21
00:01:10,270 --> 00:01:11,070
You’re right.

22
00:01:11,710 --> 00:01:13,691
Because if you two get back together,

23
00:01:13,940 --> 00:01:15,616
I’m the one who’ll look like a fool.

24
00:01:16,010 --> 00:01:18,388
North said the same—he doesn’t want to be the fool either.

25
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:20,900
Oh.

26
00:01:21,540 --> 00:01:23,162
So he’s making me the dog instead.

27
00:01:25,850 --> 00:01:27,850
That bastard North really loves me, huh?

28
00:01:29,220 --> 00:01:30,700
Alright, give me more details.

29
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,170
His name’s Kram.

30
00:01:33,230 --> 00:01:33,970
A guy?

31
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:38,460
What do you mean he’s coming back?

32
00:01:39,190 --> 00:01:41,990
He went to study in the U.S. He’s graduating now.

33
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:44,500
Why not just get back together and end it?

34
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:46,860
Let’s get back.

35
00:01:47,350 --> 00:01:48,870
Hey, hey—

36
00:03:25,930 --> 00:03:27,110
What’s your damn problem?

37
00:03:46,330 --> 00:03:47,210
Dao’s new boyfriend?

38
00:03:55,850 --> 00:03:56,640
No.

39
00:04:07,530 --> 00:04:08,180
Then who are you?

40
00:04:08,810 --> 00:04:09,635
Why are you cursing at me?

41
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:13,430
It’s my job.

42
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:15,470
What?

43
00:04:18,330 --> 00:04:19,260
Stay the hell away from him.

44
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:25,960
Oh, Dao sent you to block me?

45
00:04:27,860 --> 00:04:28,510
Yeah.

46
00:04:32,380 --> 00:04:34,760
You should pretend to be his new boyfriend.

47
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:38,520
No.

48
00:04:38,890 --> 00:04:41,688
And I don’t want to be. Just stay out of his life.

49
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:45,136
I’m not free enough to sit here and curse you out, asshole.

50
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:50,330
You’re the laziest guard dog ever.

51
00:04:50,740 --> 00:04:52,350
Why would Dao even pick you?

52
00:04:54,350 --> 00:04:56,994
Yeah, seriously. There are millions of other people.

53
00:04:57,270 --> 00:04:59,062
I can’t even complain—I still need him.

54
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:04,120
What are you to Dao?

55
00:05:14,068 --> 00:05:14,764
None of your damn business.

56
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:19,222
If you stop messing with him, that’s the end of it. Go find someone else.

57
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,838
There are tons of people better than this kid. Trust me.

58
00:05:22,150 --> 00:05:23,210
Don’t be so hung up.

59
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,740
What kind of person are you?

60
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:29,910
I’m out, asshole.

61
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:33,130
Wait. Talk to me first.

62
00:05:33,340 --> 00:05:35,420
How’s Dao? Is he doing okay?

63
00:05:37,450 --> 00:05:38,630
You idiot.

64
00:05:57,020 --> 00:05:58,030
P’Cream.

65
00:05:59,200 --> 00:05:59,670
Hm?

66
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:03,380
If you keep missing someone,

67
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,270
does that mean you love them?

68
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:14,100
Not always.

69
00:06:17,590 --> 00:06:19,250
My boyfriend killed me here.

70
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,850
In this tub.

71
00:06:21,790 --> 00:06:23,440
I still think about him every day.

72
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:27,250
If you only miss the good memories,

73
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,610
then maybe it’s love.

74
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:33,150
But if you miss the pain he caused,

75
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:38,850
then it’s not love. It’s resentment.

76
00:06:57,180 --> 00:06:58,042
What are you doing here?

77
00:06:58,790 --> 00:07:00,277
I’ve got an exam in this building too.

78
00:07:00,510 --> 00:07:02,730
I saw you sitting here, so I waited.

79
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,717
So when are you going to California?

80
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:10,310
Next week. Waiting for him to finish his exams first.

81
00:07:10,520 --> 00:07:12,070
I’m done with mine already.

82
00:07:12,690 --> 00:07:14,440
Damn, so you’re on break already?

83
00:07:15,090 --> 00:07:16,820
I’ve still got a bunch left.

84
00:07:18,090 --> 00:07:20,182
But you’ll get to travel with your boyfriend soon, right?

85
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:22,490
Yeah.

86
00:07:22,710 --> 00:07:24,829
I’m finally gonna live my life to the fullest.

87
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:28,970
Hey, you Daotok.

88
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:30,650
So,

89
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:32,130
you—

90
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,561
ever think about opening your heart?

91
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:36,022
No.

92
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,350
You asked me about this again.

93
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:41,420
I told you,

94
00:07:42,050 --> 00:07:43,990
I’m not interested in that.

95
00:07:44,090 --> 00:07:45,634
Everyone’s worried about you.

96
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:47,232
They want someone to take care of you.

97
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:49,640
And don’t say you can take care of yourself,

98
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,537
because you’re in the hospital once a month.

99
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:57,600
It’s fine if you don’t open your heart.

100
00:07:58,150 --> 00:07:59,030
But you know, right?

101
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,290
that not everyone’s an asshole like your ex.

102
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:12,150
Go.

103
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:15,050
Go where?

104
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,804
Your life’s getting way too comfortable.

105
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:22,770
Seriously.

106
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:24,010
Hey.

107
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:28,872
Every day you don’t have to earn a single dime,

108
00:08:29,250 --> 00:08:30,020
you just eat.

109
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,590
You’re getting fat.

110
00:08:37,351 --> 00:08:39,583
My friend’s talking to a dog now.

111
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:41,431
Let's go.

112
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,715
Or you’ll complain you can’t read in time again.

113
00:09:00,180 --> 00:09:01,570
What’s your problem?

114
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:04,720
Dao’s not replying to my texts.

115
00:09:07,330 --> 00:09:08,500
I’m blocking you too.

116
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:11,718
If you block me, you can’t curse at me.

117
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:15,700
Thit.

118
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:17,910
Damn it.

119
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,780
Then just come along.

120
00:09:20,950 --> 00:09:21,520
Yeah, yeah.

121
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:25,160
Shit, seriously.

122
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,500
How’s Dao doing?

123
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,460
Normal.

124
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:35,780
All 32 organs.

125
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:36,910
None missing.

126
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:39,200
Why’d he send you to block me?

127
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:40,720
Does he hate me that much?

128
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,090
If you were smarter, you wouldn’t be asking me.

129
00:09:47,470 --> 00:09:48,840
Thit, do you have a wife or something?

130
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:51,010
I’ve seen you texting for a while now.

131
00:09:51,660 --> 00:09:52,820
Wife my ass.

132
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:54,880
I’m doing guard-dog duty right now.

133
00:09:58,310 --> 00:09:59,740
For the kid next door’s ex.

134
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:01,420
Dao?

135
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,680
Yeah.

136
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,550
I can’t not do it, damn it.

137
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:08,570
I really want him back.

138
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:09,990
I regret it now.

139
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:11,860
I want another chance.

140
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:18,010
Damn, you’re seriously hopeless.

141
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:19,950
Do I look like your therapist?

142
00:10:21,210 --> 00:10:21,710
Shit.

143
00:10:40,410 --> 00:10:42,540
Go see my personal consultant.

144
00:10:42,930 --> 00:10:44,840
Guaranteed eye-opening.

145
00:10:57,540 --> 00:10:58,310
Hello.

146
00:10:59,230 --> 00:11:01,100
Arthit recommended me.

147
00:11:13,700 --> 00:11:15,620
We already had this one.

148
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:16,690
Let’s get something else.

149
00:11:22,570 --> 00:11:24,130
Oh, Dao. What are you doing here?

150
00:11:24,730 --> 00:11:26,320
I waited for him in front of his building.

151
00:11:26,710 --> 00:11:28,610
Took him to eat, then brought him here.

152
00:11:30,130 --> 00:11:31,980
I just came to buy coffee, then I’m heading back.

153
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:33,720
- Hey.
- Hey.

154
00:11:34,050 --> 00:11:34,970
Why rush off?

155
00:11:36,310 --> 00:11:37,890
I have to get back to John.

156
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:39,360
He must be lonely by now.

157
00:11:39,910 --> 00:11:42,420
You’ve got tons of ghosts in your room.

158
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,540
He’s probably playing with your cat.

159
00:11:44,936 --> 00:11:45,967
- North.
- Yes?

160
00:11:48,410 --> 00:11:49,970
That’s not the same at all.

161
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,790
Besides, everyone came with your partner.

162
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,260
Why should I stay?

163
00:11:57,770 --> 00:12:00,110
This place has so many good menu items.

164
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:01,270
Let’s order.

165
00:12:02,060 --> 00:12:02,870
You order first.

166
00:12:03,830 --> 00:12:04,551
I’ll take this one.

167
00:12:04,620 --> 00:12:06,770
Oh, P’Thit. Hi, P’.

168
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:12,670
How’d you get here?

169
00:12:12,830 --> 00:12:13,620
By car.

170
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:20,090
Good that you’re here.

171
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:21,610
Let's talk.

172
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:23,040
Now?

173
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:23,880
Yeah.

174
00:12:45,830 --> 00:12:48,410
About that guard-dog thing you asked me to do—

175
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:50,630
I texted and cursed him out.

176
00:12:53,810 --> 00:12:54,990
Kind of randomly.

177
00:12:56,190 --> 00:12:59,160
He said he wanted some advice.

178
00:12:59,370 --> 00:13:00,880
So I dumped him on Fah.

179
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:04,850
Had Fah talk to him instead.

180
00:13:06,070 --> 00:13:08,140
Maybe talking to Fah will knock some sense into him.

181
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:09,560
Mm.

182
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:10,880
Mm.

183
00:13:11,170 --> 00:13:12,430
He said

184
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:16,570
he truly feels guilty and wants to apologize to you.

185
00:13:16,950 --> 00:13:19,210
He realized he shouldn’t come back into your life.

186
00:13:20,010 --> 00:13:20,860
Fah, continue.

187
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:22,330
- Huh?
- Go on.

188
00:13:28,570 --> 00:13:31,470
He told me he treated you badly before, right?

189
00:13:34,430 --> 00:13:36,940
I don’t know the details,

190
00:13:37,370 --> 00:13:40,010
but it must’ve been serious.

191
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:45,360
He said he’s reflecting on himself now.

192
00:13:46,250 --> 00:13:47,590
But if possible,

193
00:13:48,410 --> 00:13:49,760
he’d like to try again.

194
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:57,320
I think it’s up to you, Dao.

195
00:13:58,070 --> 00:14:00,037
Whether you want to face him one more time.

196
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:03,580
Because even he isn’t sure

197
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:06,480
if he’s chasing you out of love

198
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:08,960
or just guilt.

199
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:15,120
Thank you, P’Fah.

200
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:16,810
Sure.

201
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:19,130
If I can help, I’d be more than happy to.

202
00:14:20,110 --> 00:14:21,070
Because actually,

203
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:22,660
Phoon also

204
00:14:23,930 --> 00:14:25,360
care a lot about you too.

205
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:32,890
Thanks, Maew.

206
00:14:40,710 --> 00:14:42,057
The day I'm going to talk to him,

207
00:14:45,410 --> 00:14:46,330
can you come with me?

208
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:49,300
Why?

209
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:54,050
Otherwise, You won’t be able to help at all.

210
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:56,640
I’m just asking you to block him away.

211
00:14:57,530 --> 00:14:59,644
But you still need P’Tonfah to speak for you?

212
00:15:15,580 --> 00:15:16,174
Fine.

213
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:27,430
You can go back to studying.

214
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:29,093
I can head back on my own.

215
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:31,690
Hey.

216
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:34,531
Do you think I’m a nice guy, so I’m taking you home?

217
00:15:35,860 --> 00:15:37,420
I just don’t feel like studying.

218
00:15:37,940 --> 00:15:38,968
So I’m using you as an excuse.

219
00:15:39,630 --> 00:15:40,903
Otherwise, Fah wouldn’t let me off the hook.

220
00:15:44,788 --> 00:15:45,765
You can drive, right?

221
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:52,910
Drive for me. I’m sleepy.

222
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:44,890
What are you listening to?

223
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:49,070
Want to change it?

224
00:16:50,510 --> 00:16:51,230
No need.

225
00:16:53,610 --> 00:16:54,560
It’s just kinda surprising.

226
00:16:55,230 --> 00:16:56,877
Didn’t think anyone still listened to this.

227
00:17:00,530 --> 00:17:01,250
Where are we now?

228
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:03,850
We’re lost.

229
00:17:04,340 --> 00:17:05,110
Huh?

230
00:17:06,590 --> 00:17:07,210
What the hell?

231
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:12,090
Shit, just make a U-turn up ahead.

232
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:16,560
Hey!

233
00:17:16,870 --> 00:17:18,590
Why the hell are you driving so damn slow?

234
00:17:19,670 --> 00:17:21,470
Dude, you’re going 40.

235
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:24,910
Since I was born, I’ve never driven 40 before.

236
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,350
Switch with me. I’ll drive.

237
00:17:28,570 --> 00:17:29,340
No.

238
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:47,450
Is it true med students don’t get any sleep?

239
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:50,590
Not really.

240
00:17:51,190 --> 00:17:53,250
At least I get three hours.

241
00:17:54,310 --> 00:17:56,580
Three hours? Are you insane?

242
00:17:56,620 --> 00:17:58,810
I’d rather die, seriously.

243
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:01,570
Exams are over.

244
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:03,480
I’ll catch up on sleep.

245
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:09,950
No way, you idiot!

246
00:19:10,220 --> 00:19:11,200
Ow!

247
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:15,260
Did I just blink or what the hell was that?

248
00:19:33,620 --> 00:19:34,350
Sorry.

249
00:19:35,420 --> 00:19:36,260
I forgot to return it.

250
00:19:36,950 --> 00:19:38,400
Why are you up so early?

251
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:40,600
I haven’t slept yet.

252
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:43,780
Alright, I’m off.

253
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:45,870
Hey.

254
00:19:46,980 --> 00:19:47,530
Wait.

255
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:50,754
Are you gonna tell Kram yourself, or should I talk to him?

256
00:19:54,730 --> 00:19:55,850
Talk to him for me.

257
00:19:57,830 --> 00:19:58,320
Yeah.

258
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:13,632
Are you serious?

259
00:20:13,970 --> 00:20:15,030
Dao wants to talk to me?

260
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:17,620
Yeah.

261
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:19,376
If you’re coming, come quick.

262
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:21,426
I’ve got unfinished business with him during the break.

263
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:48,680
Your ex-husband’s coming back.

264
00:21:40,190 --> 00:21:41,160
Why are you here?

265
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:42,370
Well?

266
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:44,460
I’m here to do my job.

267
00:21:45,690 --> 00:21:47,720
Are you still playing guard dog?

268
00:21:48,081 --> 00:21:48,700
Get out.

269
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,300
I asked him to come.

270
00:21:56,136 --> 00:21:56,694
You.

271
00:21:57,390 --> 00:21:59,557
If you’ve got something to say, say it. I’m going to bed.

272
00:22:03,790 --> 00:22:04,260
Dao.

273
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:06,118
How have you been?

274
00:22:08,906 --> 00:22:09,820
I’m good.

275
00:22:11,632 --> 00:22:12,777
And you?

276
00:22:15,829 --> 00:22:17,020
Not so great.

277
00:22:31,250 --> 00:22:31,770
Dao.

278
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:33,360
I…

279
00:22:33,971 --> 00:22:35,106
I’m sorry.

280
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:36,820
For everything.

281
00:22:38,557 --> 00:22:39,460
For what?

282
00:22:41,062 --> 00:22:41,480
Huh?

283
00:22:43,413 --> 00:22:44,650
What are you apologizing for?

284
00:22:46,310 --> 00:22:47,110
Say it.

285
00:22:50,460 --> 00:22:52,010
When I first pursued you,

286
00:22:53,314 --> 00:22:54,000
it was because

287
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:55,560
I made a bet with my friends.

288
00:22:57,340 --> 00:22:58,380
We said

289
00:22:59,410 --> 00:23:01,120
you’re very private

290
00:23:02,059 --> 00:23:03,068
and probably hard to win over.

291
00:23:03,706 --> 00:23:05,150
Whoever succeeded first

292
00:23:06,740 --> 00:23:07,620
would get the money.

293
00:23:11,930 --> 00:23:12,690
How much?

294
00:23:16,825 --> 00:23:17,540
How much?

295
00:23:21,708 --> 00:23:22,466
5,000.

296
00:23:25,216 --> 00:23:26,955
5,000 baht.

297
00:23:29,510 --> 00:23:31,282
Couldn’t you earn it yourself?

298
00:23:40,979 --> 00:23:42,600
Is there anything else I should know?

299
00:23:47,182 --> 00:23:48,478
But when we were together,

300
00:23:49,158 --> 00:23:50,534
my feelings for you were real.

301
00:23:52,117 --> 00:23:53,600
Then why did you cheat on me?

302
00:23:55,899 --> 00:23:56,542
Dao.

303
00:23:58,480 --> 00:23:59,580
Say it all.

304
00:24:00,820 --> 00:24:02,736
Is there anything else I should know?

305
00:24:03,590 --> 00:24:03,870
Well…

306
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:06,586
When I…

307
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,270
was dating you,

308
00:24:11,480 --> 00:24:11,750
I…

309
00:24:12,460 --> 00:24:13,672
was seeing someone else.

310
00:24:14,430 --> 00:24:16,629
I lied to you and took your money to gamble on football.

311
00:24:17,250 --> 00:24:19,201
I secretly sold your photos.

312
00:24:20,150 --> 00:24:21,795
I slept with your friend.

313
00:24:22,460 --> 00:24:24,570
I lied to you countless times.

314
00:24:26,442 --> 00:24:28,702
Even though you were so good to me.

315
00:24:28,736 --> 00:24:29,771
I’m sorry, Dao.

316
00:24:29,890 --> 00:24:32,811
- Let’s start over.
- You’ve got some nerve, asshole.

317
00:24:33,520 --> 00:24:36,270
Wait—do you even realize how fucked up you are?

318
00:24:36,693 --> 00:24:37,871
You’re seriously messed up.

319
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:39,991
You know I’m a terrible person already, right?

320
00:24:40,121 --> 00:24:43,068
But you’re on a whole different level of fucked up.

321
00:24:43,130 --> 00:24:44,617
You’re absolutely disgusting.

322
00:24:45,219 --> 00:24:46,010
You bastard.

323
00:24:47,619 --> 00:24:48,180
I get it.

324
00:24:48,731 --> 00:24:49,896
Why rub it in?

325
00:24:51,685 --> 00:24:53,370
Next time, pick a better husband.

326
00:25:01,310 --> 00:25:03,099
Do you remember when you first courted me?

327
00:25:04,877 --> 00:25:06,583
You picked me up and dropped me off every day.

328
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,690
When it rained, you gave me your shirt.

329
00:25:11,330 --> 00:25:13,297
In the mornings, you bought me grilled pork.

330
00:25:13,950 --> 00:25:16,000
In the evenings, you took me to tutoring.

331
00:25:16,700 --> 00:25:17,949
When I finished class,

332
00:25:18,410 --> 00:25:20,010
you waited to take me home.

333
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,090
I decided to love you

334
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:27,970
because no one had ever done that for me before.

335
00:25:34,840 --> 00:25:35,880
I liked you.

336
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:40,440
I liked your kindness.

337
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:43,900
But all this time,

338
00:25:45,211 --> 00:25:46,622
you never really loved me, did you?

339
00:25:47,390 --> 00:25:49,350
No, I did love you, Dao.

340
00:25:49,750 --> 00:25:51,540
- But back then, it was—
- Don’t call that love.

341
00:25:54,060 --> 00:25:55,260
It’s disgusting.

342
00:25:56,990 --> 00:25:57,373
Oops.

343
00:26:17,990 --> 00:26:19,880
Did you come back because you felt guilty?

344
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:25,600
Should I forgive someone who feels remorse?

345
00:26:29,970 --> 00:26:32,060
I’m not that kind-hearted.

346
00:26:34,410 --> 00:26:36,290
Try using your brain for once.

347
00:26:40,790 --> 00:26:41,230
Dao—

348
00:26:42,520 --> 00:26:44,590
So disappear from my life.

349
00:26:46,550 --> 00:26:48,299
I don’t even have an “it’s okay” for you.

350
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:49,780
Not even that.

351
00:26:54,460 --> 00:26:57,220
-Wait, Dao.
-That’s enough, man.

352
00:26:58,390 --> 00:27:00,470
If that were me, I’d be crushed already.

353
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:19,170
Where have you been?

354
00:27:20,900 --> 00:27:22,260
You’ve got Khun John with you now.

355
00:27:23,220 --> 00:27:25,470
Michael doesn’t need an imaginary friend anymore.

356
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,900
So why show up now?

357
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:31,070
To congratulate you.

358
00:27:32,270 --> 00:27:32,830
Michael,

359
00:27:33,280 --> 00:27:35,041
you’ve finally unlocked what was in your heart.

360
00:27:35,340 --> 00:27:38,244
From now on, you can stop thinking about him.

361
00:27:42,050 --> 00:27:43,176
I guess so.

362
00:27:44,540 --> 00:27:45,893
You can be happy now.

363
00:28:39,630 --> 00:28:40,657
Honestly,

364
00:28:41,810 --> 00:28:42,943
I was prepared.

365
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:44,940
I knew I’d get completely chewed out.

366
00:28:46,990 --> 00:28:48,460
Especially after seeing his face like that.

367
00:28:49,678 --> 00:28:50,802
It just confirmed

368
00:28:51,120 --> 00:28:52,250
that he doesn’t love me anymore.

369
00:28:53,330 --> 00:28:54,720
I really…

370
00:28:54,780 --> 00:28:56,820
don’t deserve forgiveness.

371
00:28:57,660 --> 00:28:59,470
I’ll just have to live with the guilt.

372
00:29:00,710 --> 00:29:03,130
Why do I have to sit here listening to your bullshit?

373
00:29:04,010 --> 00:29:06,180
I’ve got no one here, you know.

374
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:08,900
And I have to fly back soon.

375
00:29:10,934 --> 00:29:11,762
Alright, fine.

376
00:29:12,020 --> 00:29:12,780
Go on, say it.

377
00:29:13,550 --> 00:29:15,170
When he cursed me out,

378
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:16,860
do you think he felt better?

379
00:29:17,700 --> 00:29:18,750
Probably a bit.

380
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:20,780
Otherwise he’d keep going.

381
00:29:21,730 --> 00:29:22,620
If that’s true, that’s good.

382
00:29:24,030 --> 00:29:26,290
At least he got to vent some of his anger at me.

383
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:31,510
Let me ask you something.

384
00:29:34,380 --> 00:29:35,650
How’s Dao doing here?

385
00:29:36,210 --> 00:29:37,110
How would I know?

386
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:38,885
Aren’t you close?

387
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:40,310
Close for what?

388
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:45,540
I thought you liked Dao, so you helped him and all that.

389
00:29:46,570 --> 00:29:47,930
What the hell?

390
00:29:49,140 --> 00:29:51,750
We just had some kind of agreement, that’s all.

391
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:57,420
I…

392
00:29:58,350 --> 00:30:01,070
I’m the bastard who made Dao lose faith in love.

393
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:09,820
I need to pee.

394
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,640
I can’t hold it.

395
00:30:16,780 --> 00:30:19,420
Hey! What the hell are you doing?

396
00:30:19,750 --> 00:30:21,150
Damn it, that’s my car!

397
00:30:21,790 --> 00:30:23,510
There’s a car right next to it—why mine?!

398
00:30:23,790 --> 00:30:24,390
You idiot!

399
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:28,980
-Hey, sorry, Thit! Sorry, sorry!
-You asshole!
-Sorry, Thit!

400
00:30:29,330 --> 00:30:29,910
Shit!

401
00:30:50,770 --> 00:30:51,934
I’ve taken care of it.

402
00:31:54,170 --> 00:31:55,130
What’s up?

403
00:31:56,826 --> 00:31:57,745
I’m heading out.

404
00:31:58,340 --> 00:32:00,330
Flight’s this afternoon, asshole.

405
00:32:01,660 --> 00:32:03,783
I need to drop Khajornsak off at Maew first.

406
00:32:04,580 --> 00:32:05,050
Huh?

407
00:32:06,630 --> 00:32:07,920
Khajornsak is the cat.

408
00:32:09,430 --> 00:32:11,460
Then… what about Maew?

409
00:32:13,190 --> 00:32:14,100
P’Tonfah’s boyfriend.

410
00:32:14,770 --> 00:32:15,050
Huh?

411
00:32:17,030 --> 00:32:19,170
I’m leaving the cat with P’Tonfah’s boyfriend.

412
00:32:20,460 --> 00:32:20,860
Oh.

413
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:23,130
Yeah.

414
00:32:23,950 --> 00:32:24,410
Give me a sec.

415
00:32:24,850 --> 00:32:25,320
Ten minutes.

416
00:32:37,650 --> 00:32:38,040
Hey.

417
00:32:38,835 --> 00:32:39,115
Yeah?

418
00:32:44,830 --> 00:32:45,310
Dao.

419
00:32:50,770 --> 00:32:51,520
Thanks, man.

420
00:32:54,216 --> 00:32:54,961
For coming to help.

421
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:57,780
Mm.

422
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:59,160
It’s nothing.

423
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:04,830
What’s this guy’s name?

424
00:33:06,580 --> 00:33:07,560
Khajornsak.

425
00:33:08,630 --> 00:33:10,395
Or you can call him Khun John for short.

426
00:33:11,310 --> 00:33:12,810
What kind of cat is named Khajornsak?

427
00:33:13,530 --> 00:33:13,910
Shit.

428
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:18,005
North said you keep a snake too?

429
00:33:19,190 --> 00:33:19,560
Yeah.

430
00:33:20,970 --> 00:33:21,654
Are you scared?

431
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:27,872
I’ll go play with it sometime.

432
00:33:29,620 --> 00:33:29,940
Mm.

433
00:33:31,450 --> 00:33:32,654
And who are you leaving it with?

434
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,070
Direk.

435
00:33:35,430 --> 00:33:37,285
He’s old already. Might as well stay home and babysit his grandkid.

436
00:33:40,960 --> 00:33:42,260
What did your dad say?

437
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:46,070
Direk?

438
00:33:48,930 --> 00:33:49,940
He didn’t say anything.

439
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:52,950
I think Direk has come to terms with it.

440
00:33:56,380 --> 00:33:57,070
I’m the only one

441
00:33:59,710 --> 00:34:00,750
who still can’t accept it.

442
00:34:28,422 --> 00:34:29,629
If you’re still around,

443
00:34:29,998 --> 00:34:31,050
come visit our son sometimes.

444
00:34:44,810 --> 00:34:46,845
He misses you so much, you know.

445
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:02,530
Is it good?

446
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:14,460
Hello, Khun John.

447
00:35:16,870 --> 00:35:17,810
So cute.

448
00:35:18,190 --> 00:35:21,350
Be good, okay? No being naughty, Khun John.

449
00:35:22,110 --> 00:35:23,120
Please take care of him.

450
00:35:23,470 --> 00:35:23,850
Hey.

451
00:35:26,035 --> 00:35:26,497
Yeah?

452
00:35:28,570 --> 00:35:29,920
Take good care of him.

453
00:35:31,830 --> 00:35:32,600
Me?

454
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:33,970
Yeah, you.

455
00:35:34,817 --> 00:35:36,266
You asked him to help you.

456
00:35:36,490 --> 00:35:37,928
So you better take good care of him, got it?

457
00:35:42,237 --> 00:35:42,653
Hey.

458
00:35:43,570 --> 00:35:46,299
He went all the way across the world to help you.

459
00:35:46,751 --> 00:35:47,899
Has he ever complained

460
00:35:48,158 --> 00:35:49,831
or shown any sign of being upset?

461
00:35:52,727 --> 00:35:53,325
Never.

462
00:35:55,248 --> 00:35:56,608
Phoon once told me

463
00:35:56,940 --> 00:35:58,670
that talking to spirits like that

464
00:35:59,845 --> 00:36:01,440
drains his life energy.

465
00:36:02,630 --> 00:36:03,440
So

466
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:06,272
just take good care of him.

467
00:36:07,260 --> 00:36:08,790
That shouldn’t be too much for you.

468
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:11,960
Yeah, yeah, I know, Fah.

469
00:36:12,780 --> 00:36:13,970
Stop nagging.

470
00:36:15,110 --> 00:36:16,270
Look at how you act.

471
00:36:21,260 --> 00:36:22,700
- Have a safe trip, man.
- Safe travels.

472
00:36:24,990 --> 00:36:26,830
Please take care of Khun John.

473
00:36:27,830 --> 00:36:27,980
Mm.

474
00:36:28,512 --> 00:36:29,164
Don’t worry.

475
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:31,706
Dao, take good care of yourself too.

476
00:36:32,060 --> 00:36:33,294
Eat your meals on time.

477
00:36:36,167 --> 00:36:37,308
Have a safe flight.

478
00:36:38,032 --> 00:36:38,534
Yeah.

479
00:36:39,202 --> 00:36:39,961
Nong Dao.

480
00:36:40,200 --> 00:36:41,542
Have a safe trip.

481
00:36:42,017 --> 00:36:42,952
Thank you.

482
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:46,690
We should go now.

483
00:36:53,014 --> 00:36:54,665
Going with Arthit, just the two of them.

484
00:36:55,320 --> 00:36:56,940
I'm starting to worry about Dao.

485
00:36:59,390 --> 00:37:00,350
No need to worry.

486
00:37:01,190 --> 00:37:02,420
Even he look quiet

487
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:03,670
but he’s a fighter.

488
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:05,430
Dao is

489
00:37:05,730 --> 00:37:06,700
really strong.

490
00:37:09,630 --> 00:37:10,830
Just like Phoon now.

491
00:37:13,354 --> 00:37:13,900
Let's go.

492
00:37:25,400 --> 00:37:26,310
Are you okay?

493
00:37:27,571 --> 00:37:28,245
I’m fine.

494
00:37:28,870 --> 00:37:29,995
It’s just a sneeze.

495
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:32,727
Don’t get sick while you’re with me.

496
00:37:33,670 --> 00:37:35,521
Or Fah’s gonna chew me out again.

497
00:37:35,785 --> 00:37:37,074
He’ll say I didn’t take care of you.

498
00:37:53,878 --> 00:37:54,469
Hey.

499
00:37:56,398 --> 00:37:57,087
Do you have another one?

500
00:37:59,337 --> 00:37:59,948
Hey.

501
00:38:34,730 --> 00:38:35,230
Hey.

502
00:38:36,869 --> 00:38:38,054
Do you have another pair of earphones?

503
00:38:38,896 --> 00:38:40,174
I forgot to bring mine.

504
00:38:42,002 --> 00:38:42,648
Hey.

505
00:38:44,042 --> 00:38:44,737
Nope.

506
00:38:46,254 --> 00:38:46,979
Then—

507
00:38:48,217 --> 00:38:49,937
- Can I borrow one side?
- No.

508
00:38:52,620 --> 00:38:53,370
You’re so heartless.

509
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,100
Your playlist’s really good.

510
00:39:44,250 --> 00:39:44,910
Share it with me.

511
00:39:46,995 --> 00:39:47,577
Mm.

512
00:39:48,259 --> 00:39:49,171
I’ll share it.

513
00:39:54,982 --> 00:39:55,840
Which one do you want?

514
00:39:57,315 --> 00:39:57,948
All of them.

515
00:40:25,914 --> 00:40:26,525
What are you drawing?

516
00:40:29,214 --> 00:40:30,521
A scene from a novel.

517
00:40:33,002 --> 00:40:33,795
That’s really nice.

518
00:40:34,623 --> 00:40:35,666
You can hire me.

519
00:40:36,576 --> 00:40:37,773
You’re good at selling yourself.

520
00:40:39,112 --> 00:40:40,017
A little.

521
00:40:49,870 --> 00:40:51,800
Emma, do you like to painting?

522
00:40:56,862 --> 00:40:57,717
I do.

523
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:02,030
How about you, Dylan? What do you like?

524
00:41:02,970 --> 00:41:04,482
I like music.

525
00:41:06,130 --> 00:41:10,190
Then when you grow up, you will be an amazing musician.

526
00:41:12,340 --> 00:41:12,690
No.

527
00:41:13,780 --> 00:41:16,804
When I grow up, I’m going to be a doctor.

528
00:41:19,810 --> 00:41:20,420
Why so?

529
00:41:23,510 --> 00:41:25,120
So I can treat you.

530
00:41:44,459 --> 00:41:45,128
Mom.

531
00:41:46,051 --> 00:41:46,680
I’m home.

532
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:52,400
Your house is so tidy.

533
00:41:54,240 --> 00:41:55,950
Direk always has someone clean it.

534
00:41:58,150 --> 00:41:59,350
Even if we only come once a year.

535
00:42:01,670 --> 00:42:02,830
You and your dad?

536
00:42:04,190 --> 00:42:04,710
Mm.

537
00:42:06,390 --> 00:42:07,500
We come back around Christmas.

538
00:42:10,310 --> 00:42:11,650
There’s a guest room at my place.

539
00:42:12,690 --> 00:42:13,370
You can sleep there.

540
00:42:14,870 --> 00:42:15,450
Let’s go inside.

541
00:42:32,700 --> 00:42:33,370
Hey, hey.

542
00:42:34,390 --> 00:42:35,270
You don’t eat the skin?

543
00:42:36,740 --> 00:42:37,140
No.

544
00:42:38,650 --> 00:42:39,080
Seriously?

545
00:42:39,640 --> 00:42:40,080
Why?

546
00:42:41,110 --> 00:42:42,060
I don’t like it.

547
00:42:42,220 --> 00:42:42,860
It’s hard.

548
00:42:43,438 --> 00:42:44,160
It pokes my gums.

549
00:42:45,140 --> 00:42:46,530
No way.

550
00:42:46,890 --> 00:42:48,480
You’re disrespecting fried chicken.

551
00:42:48,790 --> 00:42:52,100
They worked so hard to make it crispy. You can’t do that. That ruins the whole system.

552
00:42:52,230 --> 00:42:53,940
No, no—give it here. I’ll eat it.

553
00:42:54,710 --> 00:42:55,000
Here.

554
00:42:55,706 --> 00:42:56,320
The meat.

555
00:42:56,869 --> 00:42:57,321
Give it to me.

556
00:43:05,300 --> 00:43:07,133
It feels so nice here.

557
00:43:10,877 --> 00:43:11,869
My mom liked this spot.

558
00:43:13,810 --> 00:43:14,650
I can tell.

559
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:23,710
She liked drawing too.

560
00:43:26,630 --> 00:43:27,070
Really?

561
00:43:29,100 --> 00:43:29,520
Mm.

562
00:43:33,390 --> 00:43:35,351
You said you take drawing commissions, right?

563
00:43:36,190 --> 00:43:36,470
Mm.

564
00:43:38,125 --> 00:43:39,016
Then I’m hiring you.

565
00:43:41,235 --> 00:43:42,124
To do what?

566
00:43:43,570 --> 00:43:45,441
Finish the drawings my mom left unfinished.

567
00:44:31,478 --> 00:44:32,262
These ones.

568
00:44:34,121 --> 00:44:35,943
She drew them when she was very sick.

569
00:44:38,242 --> 00:44:40,231
But she passed away before she could finish them.

570
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:08,230
She’d probably like this spot.

571
00:45:17,470 --> 00:45:17,970
It feels

572
00:45:20,970 --> 00:45:21,560
warm.

573
00:45:33,360 --> 00:45:34,210
Is my mom still here?

574
00:45:36,820 --> 00:45:37,600
I’m not sure.

575
00:45:39,870 --> 00:45:42,570
It feels like when we were at your dad’s house.

576
00:45:45,910 --> 00:45:46,640
But right now,

577
00:45:50,340 --> 00:45:51,050
I don’t see her.

578
00:45:58,120 --> 00:45:59,840
Is it really okay for me to finish these?

579
00:46:06,310 --> 00:46:08,230
I think if someone finishes them,

580
00:46:09,570 --> 00:46:10,790
adds beautiful colors,

581
00:46:15,190 --> 00:46:16,590
my mom would be happy.

582
00:46:21,300 --> 00:46:21,790
Okay.

583
00:46:35,440 --> 00:46:35,750
Hey.

584
00:46:36,650 --> 00:46:36,830
Hmm?

585
00:46:39,830 --> 00:46:40,570
In case...

586
00:46:42,028 --> 00:46:42,970
Just in case.

587
00:46:46,070 --> 00:46:47,530
If my mom were really still here,

588
00:46:51,380 --> 00:46:53,543
is there a way for me to see her?

589
00:46:55,100 --> 00:46:56,974
Like how Meen can see Do?

590
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,014
Do you think

591
00:46:59,730 --> 00:47:01,957
humans and ghosts can really live together?

592
00:47:04,420 --> 00:47:06,044
Technically, they shouldn’t.

593
00:47:07,260 --> 00:47:09,565
Then why can Do and Meen stay together?

594
00:47:10,540 --> 00:47:12,940
Because Do still has unfinished business.

595
00:47:19,370 --> 00:47:21,077
And Meen is still holding on.

596
00:47:43,225 --> 00:47:44,777
Time to stop dreaming.

597
00:47:49,310 --> 00:47:52,130
I used up all the courage I had to make this decision.

598
00:47:58,241 --> 00:47:59,542
I love you, Meen.

599
00:48:04,072 --> 00:48:04,792
So much.

600
00:48:06,180 --> 00:48:06,690
But.

601
00:48:12,440 --> 00:48:13,060
I have to go.

602
00:48:45,690 --> 00:48:46,470
Do.

603
00:48:53,890 --> 00:48:55,602
Where are you, Do?

604
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:03,930
Do.

605
00:49:12,330 --> 00:49:16,960
Grandma once told me that the world of the living and the world of the dead can intersect.

606
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:21,780
But in the end, we learn that love means letting go.

607
00:49:22,570 --> 00:49:24,480
Letting the dead rest in peace.

608
00:49:26,490 --> 00:49:28,650
And letting the living move on with their lives.

609
00:49:34,430 --> 00:49:35,540
Yeah? What’s up?

610
00:49:35,720 --> 00:49:36,130
Go on.

611
00:49:38,050 --> 00:49:38,430
Direk.

612
00:49:42,310 --> 00:49:43,570
What if I don’t find her?

613
00:49:45,640 --> 00:49:46,450
I’m just...

614
00:49:49,718 --> 00:49:51,081
I really pushed it, Direk.

615
00:49:53,337 --> 00:49:55,054
I came all this way.

616
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:58,640
There’s nothing you can do. You know that.

617
00:50:00,520 --> 00:50:01,940
And going that far—

618
00:50:02,280 --> 00:50:04,810
wasn’t it so you could be sure and finally let go?

619
00:50:08,430 --> 00:50:09,710
Have you really let go, Direk?

620
00:50:10,980 --> 00:50:11,420
Yeah.

621
00:50:12,520 --> 00:50:13,670
How did you do it?

622
00:50:15,460 --> 00:50:16,710
Because I have you.

623
00:50:18,610 --> 00:50:19,653
That’s unexpectedly touching.

624
00:50:20,300 --> 00:50:22,770
Hey, I was about to get emotional and you ruined it.

625
00:50:25,680 --> 00:50:26,770
Go on.

626
00:50:28,110 --> 00:50:30,260
Let me get so moved I cry, okay?

627
00:50:31,530 --> 00:50:33,190
You’re such a pain. I’m not talking anymore.

628
00:50:34,400 --> 00:50:35,510
If you can mess with me like this,

629
00:50:36,060 --> 00:50:37,160
that means you’re doing better, right?

630
00:50:38,150 --> 00:50:39,000
A little.

631
00:50:40,210 --> 00:50:40,610
That’s good.

632
00:50:41,030 --> 00:50:41,660
Alright then.

633
00:50:42,770 --> 00:50:45,130
I’ve gotta get back to work. Gotta earn money to feed the buffalo.

634
00:50:47,690 --> 00:50:49,330
Yeah, I’ll call you later.

635
00:50:50,130 --> 00:50:50,630
That’s it.

636
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:00,790
Oh.

637
00:51:02,900 --> 00:51:04,030
I was about to come up and see you.

638
00:51:05,990 --> 00:51:07,090
Got carried away with the drawing.

639
00:51:09,080 --> 00:51:09,870
But it’s not finished yet.

640
00:51:11,240 --> 00:51:12,190
No rush.

641
00:51:12,780 --> 00:51:13,530
Take your time.

642
00:51:20,670 --> 00:51:21,530
This chair—

643
00:51:24,470 --> 00:51:25,430
my mom died right there.

644
00:51:27,880 --> 00:51:28,800
Can I sit?

645
00:51:32,140 --> 00:51:32,530
Yeah.

646
00:52:19,788 --> 00:52:20,915
What’s wrong?

647
00:52:28,909 --> 00:52:30,130
This place—

648
00:52:33,318 --> 00:52:35,391
is where she passed away.

649
00:52:42,785 --> 00:52:43,522
Emma.

650
00:52:43,545 --> 00:52:44,651
Wake up.

651
00:52:46,527 --> 00:52:47,281
Wake up.

652
00:52:48,130 --> 00:52:50,042
Mom, please wake up.

653
00:52:50,948 --> 00:52:52,084
Mom.

654
00:52:54,155 --> 00:52:55,650
Please wake up.

655
00:53:00,571 --> 00:53:01,475
Direk.

656
00:53:02,211 --> 00:53:03,020
Direk.

657
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:11,395
Dad.

658
00:53:26,127 --> 00:53:27,666
It was Christmas, right?

659
00:53:33,794 --> 00:53:35,202
Your mom—

660
00:53:38,527 --> 00:53:40,146
she was very happy.

661
00:53:48,828 --> 00:53:51,139
She wasn’t in any pain at all.

662
00:53:55,509 --> 00:53:58,505
She must have made peace with her death.

663
00:54:01,164 --> 00:54:02,671
But she probably regretted—

664
00:54:07,334 --> 00:54:10,642
that she wouldn’t get to watch you grow up anymore.

665
00:54:19,454 --> 00:54:21,063
She wasn’t in pain at all.

666
00:54:24,040 --> 00:54:25,207
It’s just that—

667
00:54:33,856 --> 00:54:35,269
she’s not here anymore.

668
00:54:52,038 --> 00:54:53,571
She’s at peace now.

669
00:55:09,517 --> 00:55:11,856
There’s still love left here.

670
00:55:12,844 --> 00:55:14,320
I can feel it.

671
00:55:15,835 --> 00:55:18,386
There’s no pain or sadness at all.

672
00:55:19,874 --> 00:55:21,463
But she’s not here anymore.

673
00:55:23,786 --> 00:55:25,195
Not here—

674
00:55:27,752 --> 00:55:28,955
or anywhere.

675
00:55:33,354 --> 00:55:34,634
She’s gone.

676
00:55:54,077 --> 00:55:55,629
Hey, do you have a crush on someone?

677
00:55:55,988 --> 00:55:57,419
Are you crazy? I don’t like anyone.

678
00:55:57,954 --> 00:55:58,690
Hey—

679
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:16,619
Idiot. That’s suspicious as hell.

680
00:56:17,755 --> 00:56:21,340
Can you help me out? P’Arthit lost his keycard.

